criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age over 16 years;

          -  Classified as high-risk by the SAMPE Risk Model (30-day mortality >5%);

          -  Underwent non-cardiac surgeries at the main operating room unit;

          -  Referred postoperatively to the postanesthesia care unit or intensive care unit.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients undergoing procedures performed outside the operating room unit (outpatient,
             diagnostic, performed under local anesthesia);

          -  Patients undergoing cardiac surgery with cardiopulmonary bypass and / or referred to
             the cardiac ICU postoperatively;

          -  Patients undergoing organ transplantation;

          -  Low-risk patients (classified as <5% probability of death within 30 days by the SAMPE
             Risk Model).
